\chapter{Querying Commit Data}
\label{commits}

The viewer (\cref{viewer}), the exporter (\cref{progsnap2}),
and the [[list]] command (\cref{sec:list-command}) all need to
list commits and fetch details for individual commits.
We keep these as standalone functions rather than methods on
[[LearnlogRepo]]---the repo class handles \emph{recording}; these
functions handle \emph{reading}, which is a different concern.

Separating reading from recording also avoids circular imports:
several modules depend on these functions, but none of them need
to import the CLI module.


