\section{Tag resolution}
\label{sec:tag-resolution}

Git tags let users mark meaningful points in a development
log---for instance, the start of each lab session.
We need a mapping from commit hashes to tag names for two
purposes: the ProgSnap2 exporter adds an [[X-Tag]] column
to the event table (\cref{progsnap2}), and the [[play]]
command resolves tag names to starting commits
(\cref{sec:play}).

We query all tags in a single [[git tag -l]] call rather
than checking each commit individually, because the number
of tags is small (typically one per lab session) and a
single subprocess call is cheaper than one per commit.

<<commits functions>>=
def get_tag_map(repo):
    """Map commit hashes to tag names.

    Returns a dict where keys are full commit hashes
    and values are lists of tag names pointing at that
    commit.
    """
    result = repo.git(
        "tag", "-l",
        "--format=%(objectname) %(refname:short)",
    )
    if result.returncode != 0:
        return {}
    tag_map = {}
    for line in result.stdout.strip().split("\n"):
        if not line:
            continue
        parts = line.split(" ", 1)
        if len(parts) == 2:
            commit_hash, tag_name = parts
            tag_map.setdefault(
                commit_hash, []
            ).append(tag_name)
    return tag_map
@

Let's verify that the tag map correctly associates commits
with their tags:

<<commits test functions>>=
def test_get_tag_map_single_tag(workdir):
    """A tag on HEAD appears in the map."""
    from learnlog.commits import get_tag_map, get_commits
    repo = LearnlogRepo(workdir)
    repo.git("tag", "lab1")
    commits = get_commits(repo)
    tag_map = get_tag_map(repo)
    assert "lab1" in tag_map[commits[-1]["hash"]]

def test_get_tag_map_multiple_tags(workdir):
    """Multiple tags on the same commit all appear."""
    from learnlog.commits import get_tag_map, get_commits
    repo = LearnlogRepo(workdir)
    repo.git("tag", "lab1")
    repo.git("tag", "milestone")
    commits = get_commits(repo)
    tags = tag_map = get_tag_map(repo)
    names = tags[commits[-1]["hash"]]
    assert "lab1" in names
    assert "milestone" in names

def test_get_tag_map_no_tags(workdir):
    """A repo with no tags returns an empty map."""
    from learnlog.commits import get_tag_map
    repo = LearnlogRepo(workdir)
    tag_map = get_tag_map(repo)
    assert tag_map == {}
